event: The mouse clicked on # start. The mouse is clicking on the Start button.
description: The mouse click on the Start button caused the Start Menu to expand.

event: The mouse clicked on ContrqPanel. The mouse is clicking on the "Control Panel" menu item in the start menu.
description: The user clicked on the "Control Panel" item in the Start Menu, causing the tooltip associated with the item to disappear.
outcome: The "Control Panel" option's tooltip disappeared from view.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Appearance and Themes" icon in the Control Panel window.
description: The user clicked on the "Appearance and Themes" icon in the Control Panel window.
outcome: The text box describing the "Appearance and Themes" category's function disappeared.

event: The mouse clicked on splay. The mouse is clicking on the "Display" Control Panel icon.
description: The mouse click on the "Display" icon in the Appearance and Themes window opened the Display Properties window.
outcome: The Display Properties window opened and the mouse cursor changed to a left-click pointer icon upon hovering over the "Display" icon.

event: The mouse clicked on DesktopScreen SverAppearanceSettings. The mouse is clicking on the "Screen Saver" tab of the Display Properties window.
description: The user clicked the "Screen Saver" tab in the "Display Properties" window. As a result, the window's content switched to the "Screen Saver" settings, replacing the previously displayed "Themes" tab content.
outcome: The "Display Properties" window switched to the "Screen Saver" tab. The preview area now displays a monitor icon with a sample window against a blue background. The "Save As...", "Delete", and dropdown menu are no longer visible.

event: The mouse is clicking on the down arrow of the "Screen saver" drop-down list.
description: The user clicked the down arrow of the "Screen saver" drop-down list to open it.
outcome: The "Screen Saver" dropdown menu opened, displaying the available screensavers. Simultaneously, the "Settings" button became grayed out.

event: The mouse is clicking on "3D FlowerBox" in the "Screen Saver" dropdown menu.
description: The user clicked on the "3D FlowerBox" option within the "Screen Saver" dropdown menu.
outcome: The "3D FlowerBox" option was selected in the  "Screen Saver" dropdown menu, and the "Settings" button became enabled.

event: The mouse clicked on Pow. The mouse is clicking on the "Power" button.
description: The user clicked the "Power" button at the bottom of the "Display Properties" window. This opened the "Power Options Properties" window.
outcome: The "Power Options Properties" window came into view, with the "Home/Office Desk" power scheme selected. The previously highlighted "Power" button is no longer visible.

event: The mouse is clicking on the dropdown arrow for the "Turn off monitor" setting.
description: The user clicked the dropdown arrow of the "Turn off monitor:" setting.
outcome: The dropdown menu for the "Turn off monitor" setting opened, displaying the available time options.

event: The mouse clicked on After 5 hours. The mouse is clicking on "After 2 hours" in the dropdown menu for "Turn off monitor:".
description: The user clicked on "After 2 hours" in the "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu, changing the setting from "After 20 mins" to "After 2 hours" for the "Home/Office Desk" power scheme.
outcome: The "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu closed, with "After 2 hours" now displayed as the selected option.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Save As..." button.
description: The user clicks the "Save As..." button located in the "Power Schemes" tab of the "Power Options Properties" window.
outcome: The "Save As" dialog box opened, prompting the user to enter a scheme name and choose a save location.

event: The mouse clicked on Always On. The mouse is clicking on the "Minimal Power Management" item in the "Power schemes" dropdown menu of the "Power Options Properties" window.
description: The user selected "Minimal Power Management" from the "Power schemes" dropdown menu in the "Power Options Properties" window.
outcome: The "Power schemes" dropdown menu closed, and the "Settings for 'Minimal Power Management' power scheme" section updated to reflect the selected scheme.

event: The mouse is clicking on the dropdown arrow for "Turn off hard disks".
description: The user clicks the dropdown arrow for the "Turn off hard disks" option, located under the "Settings for 'Minimal Power Management' power scheme" section of the "Power Options Properties" window.
outcome: The dropdown menu for the "Turn off hard disks" option opened.

event: The mouse is clicking on the dropdown arrow of the "Turn off monitor" option.
description: The user clicks the dropdown arrow of the "Turn off monitor" option within the "Settings for 'Minimal Power Management' power scheme" section.
outcome: The dropdown menu for the "Turn off monitor" option opened.

event: The mouse clicked on Never. The mouse is clicking on "Never" in the dropdown menu for "System hibernates".
description: The user clicked on "Never" in the "System hibernates" dropdown menu under the "Settings for 'Minimal Power Management' power scheme" section. As a result, "Never" is now displayed as the selected option for "System hibernates".
outcome: The "System hibernates" dropdown menu, previously open, is now closed. The selected option displayed within the menu has changed to "Never".

event: The mouse clicked on OK. The mouse is clicking on the "Cancel" button of the Power Options Properties window.
description: The user clicked the "Cancel" button at the bottom of the "Power Options Properties" window. As a result, no changes were applied to the power scheme settings, and the window remained open.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "OK" button.
description: The user clicks the "OK" button in the "Display Properties" window to confirm the selection of "None" for the screensaver.

event: Mouse click on the close button of the window titled "Appearance and Themes".
description: The user clicked on the close button of the "Appearance and Themes" window. As a result, the "Appearance and Themes" window is closed.
outcome: The "Appearance and Themes" window closed, and the user was returned to the Control Panel window.
